<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Gutierrezia</i> <i>microcephala</i> and/or <i>Gutierrezia</i> <i>sarothrae</i> is dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Atriplex</i> spp., <i>Cylindropuntia</i> <i>acanthocarpa</i>, <i>Ephedra</i> <i>nevadensis</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>wrightii</i>, <i>Krascheninnikovia</i> <i>lanata</i>, <i>Larrea</i> <i>tridentata</i>, <i>Opuntia</i> <i>polyacantha</i> var. <i>erinacea</i>, <i>Prunus</i> <i>fasciculata</i>, <i>Sphaeralcea</i> <i>ambigua</i>, <i>Stephanomeria</i> <i>pauciflora</i> and <i>Yucca</i> <i>schidigera</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 1.5 m; canopy is open to intermittent. Herbaceous layer is absent to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Gutierrezia sarothrae</i> or <i>G. microcephala</i> > 50% relative cover and clearly dominant (Evens et al. 2014).</li>
		
		<li><i>Gutierrezia sarothrae</i>  > 50% relative cover with sometimes higher cover of herbs (Evens and San 2005).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Hill, ridges, valleys, cliffs, plateaus, moderate to somewhat steep slopes, and draws in desert or desert-transition vegetation. Soils are typically loams often well drained.  </div>
</div>

        
