    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        
            <p><i>Gutierrezia </i>species occur in a broader range than is currently cited for the alliance. More sampling and comparison with other early- to late-seral types are needed to determine the alliance's full variation and extent.</p>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Mojave Desert</b> (322Af-g, Aj-l, An). Stands have been sampled in the Clark and New York Mountains of the Mojave National Preserve and in the Panamint Range of Death Valley National Park (Evens et al. 2014). The alliance has been mapped occasionally in western subsections of the Mojave Desert (VegCAMP and AIS 2013).</li>
        
            <li><b>Southern California Mountains and Valleys</b> (M262Bn-o). Stands in the foothills west of and on Volcan Mountain in the Palomar-Cuyamaca Peak areas of San Diego Co. had an understory of <i>Avena barbata, Bromus hordeaceus, Erodium</i> spp., and <i>Nassella pulchra</i> (Moran 2004b, Evens and San 2005). More sampling is needed to understand the full extent of this alliance in the section.</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> A long history of settlement and livestock grazing has impacted the native vegetation in the desert regions where this alliance occurs. Stands of this alliance typically occur in recently disturbed sites such as burned areas, steep cliffs with colluvial rockfall, minor drainages with intermittent flooding, and heavily grazed or recently cleared areas. A variety of graminoids and forbs often occur in these stands, including <i>Achnatherum speciosum, Aristida purpurea, Bromus rubens, Bromus tectorum, Elymus elymoides, Pleuraphis jamesii, Pleuraphis rigida,</i>and <i>Sphaeralcea ambigua</i>. The shrubs of this alliance are opportunistic sub-shrubs and will transition over time to other alliances. </div>
</div>

    

    

    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
